    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 lbs mutton, cut into pieces</li>
            <li>2 large onions, finely sliced</li>
            <li>1/2 cup plain yogurt</li>
            <li>1/4 cup cashews, soaked in water</li>
            <li>1/4 cup almonds, blanched</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ghee or vegetable oil</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground turmeric</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground coriander</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cardamom powder</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon saffron strands (optional)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Chopped fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Sliced almonds for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>nonveg</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a blender, grind soaked cashews and blanched almonds into a smooth paste with a little water.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, heat ghee or vegetable oil. Saut√© sliced onions until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add mutton pieces and brown on all sides.</li>
            <li>Stir in yogurt, ground turmeric, red chili powder, ground coriander, garam masala, cardamom powder, and saffron strands (if using).</li>
            <li>Add the nut paste and cook until the oil separates from the masala.</li>
            <li>Pour in enough water to cover the mutton, add salt, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer until the meat is tender.</li>
            <li>Adjust salt and spice levels to taste.</li>
            <li>Garnish with chopped cilantro and sliced almonds.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with naan or steamed rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Mutton Korma!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
